# CORS for upload images — enables the worship-slides announcement carousel.
#
# The slides editor (apps/slides in the ../hocuspocus repo, a separate origin)
# pulls the curated carousel feed and bakes the pre-/post-service announcement
# loop into a GIF. To bake an image it must read its bytes via fetch() and inline
# them as a data URL, and a cross-origin fetch needs the image response to permit
# it. Apache serves /wp-content/uploads/* as static files (bypassing PHP), so a
# plugin / mu-plugin hook can never add this header — it has to live here.
#
# Scope: already-public images, GET only. Nothing private is exposed. If
# mod_headers is unavailable the block is skipped and slide backgrounds simply
# fall back to solid colors (the carousel still works).
<IfModule mod_headers.c>
  <FilesMatch "(?i)\.(jpe?g|png|gif|webp|avif|svg)$">
    Header set Access-Control-Allow-Origin "*"
    Header set Access-Control-Allow-Methods "GET, OPTIONS"
    Header append Vary "Origin"
  </FilesMatch>
</IfModule>
